  m_text: "Flammable liquids are heated in a water bath and non-flammable liquids
    are heated directly over the flame in a test tube.\n\nWhile heating a test tube,
    its angle should be maintained at 45\xB0.\n\nKeep the mouth of the test tube
    facing away from everyone.\n\nHeat the test tube at the surface of the liquid
    to avoid bumping."
